				"synopsis": {
					"type": 23,
					"value": "| A social worker in charge of a refugee hostel is speaking with a father and his child, both of whom are seeking refuge. The social worker informs the father that, in order to prevent the spread of lice in the hostel, he must burn his child's clothes and thoroughly clean the child's hair. The social worker is concerned with maintaining order and ensuring that everyone in the hostel has a safe and clean place to stay. \r\nThe family lost their mother and the father does not know how to take care of the kid properly.|"
